1 Install Erlang, set home
2 Set RabbitMQ environments
3 Install RabbitMQ
4 Enable management, shovel and shovel management
5 Add a new user on both VM's with same password.
6 VM1 Client ->Oubound 5671, VM2 Server-> Inbound 5671
7 Make a test shovel with tcp listner 5671 (5672 must also avaliable on host) on VM1
8 Make the queues on VM1, if the shovel is started
9 On VM2 queues should now be autogenerated.

* TCP 5671 Success

SSL VM2:
1 Make CSR
2 When CSR approved is back, import certificate in personal
3 Make Bundle of Root, CA
4 Export personal as pkx
5 Get the private key
5.1 For this you need OpenSSL 1.1.1 or lower
Win32/Win64 OpenSSL Installer for Windows - Shining Light Productions (slproweb.com)
* The Win32/Win64 OpenSSL Installation Project is dedicated to providing a simple installation of OpenSSL for Microsoft Windows. 
* Win64 OpenSSL v1.1.1m MSI (63MB Installer)

6 Generate pem from pkx
7 Update config, ssl listner, ssl options
8 Check connection
* SSL success


